# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# NexusGate — Environment Configuration Example
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Guidelines:
# 1. Copy this file to '.env' for local development.
# 2. Environment variables take precedence over settings in 'config.toml'.
# 3. Use 'DATABASE_<ALIAS>_URL' to inject secrets to specific database nodes.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# --- Global Orchestration ---
# Path to the primary configuration TOML.
# NEXUSGATE_CONFIG=./config.toml

# --- Observability ---
# Severity level for the structured logger (TRACE | DEBUG | INFO | WARN | ERROR).
# NEXUSGATE_LOG_LEVEL=DEBUG

# --- Infrastructure Backends ---
# Primary Redis connection string for Caching and Distributed Rate Limiting.
# REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379/0

# --- Database Tier (Dynamic Injection) ---
# Format: DATABASE_<ALIAS_IN_UPPERCASE>_URL
# DATABASE_MAIN_DB_URL=sqlite:///./data/main.db
# DATABASE_ANALYTICS_URL=postgresql://user:pass@localhost:5432/analytics

# --- Federation & Security ---
# Webhook signing secret (Global default if not specified per-hook in TOML).
# NEXUSGATE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=your_32_char_signing_secret_here
